            - person: person-renly-baratheon
              role: spectator
        properties:
            also_known_as: "The Hand's Tourney"
            description: "A great tournament held at King's Landing, nominally in honor of Ned Stark as Hand but against his wishes. Key jousting outcomes: Sandor Clegane defeated Jaime Lannister (second pass). Loras Tyrell defeated Ser Gregor Clegane using a mare in heat to unsettle Gregor's stallion. After losing, Gregor killed his horse and attacked Loras; Sandor intervened and the brothers fought until Robert halted it. Loras conceded the champion's purse to Sandor. Ser Hugh of the Vale was killed in the jousting — lance driven through throat under gorget. Anguy won the archery. Thoros of Myr won the melee with a flaming sword. Robert was talked out of participating in the melee by Ned and Ser Barristan. The prize was twenty thousand gold dragons."
